The smart part

The “profile” is not just the Pokémon species.

It is the best representation of that Pokémon.

That means each Pokémon’s profile contains:
	•	hero image
	•	alternate art gallery
	•	shiny palette
	•	sprites
	•	anime art or game render
	•	favorite cards featuring that Pokémon
	•	maybe top fan-favorite poses

So the question becomes:

“Do I like this Pokémon’s whole aesthetic and vibe more?”

That is way more accurate than comparing names alone.

