Best user flow

1. Start screen

“Let’s find your favorite Pokémon.”

Choose:
	•	All Pokémon
	•	Original 151 only
	•	Favorites by generation
	•	Legendary/Mythical included or excluded
	•	Final evolutions only
	•	Starter lines only
	•	Cute / Cool / Weird / Strong / Gremlin filters

2. Seed round

Ask for a few starting preferences:

“Pick a starter champion”
	•	Pikachu
	•	Charizard
	•	Umbreon
	•	Gengar
	•	Eevee
	•	Random

This avoids starting from total randomness.

3. Swipe rounds

Champion stays until defeated.

That creates attachment and drama.

4. On Deck

A holding area for “close calls.”

This matters a lot because sometimes you do not want to eliminate a Pokémon forever, you just do not know yet.

5. Final showdown

Once enough comparisons happen, the app surfaces:
	•	Top 10
	•	Final 4
	•	Championship bracket

Then you do the last few comparisons manually.

6. Results page

“You favorite Pokémon is: Umbreon”
with:
	•	runner-up
	•	top 10
	•	type breakdown
	•	region bias
	•	personality summary

