Why the app works psychologically

It removes the hardest part: having to remember every Pokémon and compare them all in your head.

Instead it uses:
	•	small decisions
	•	visual comparison
	•	momentum
	•	pattern emergence

After 30–100 swipes, your taste starts revealing itself.

That is satisfying.

⸻

Better than simple swiping: hidden ranking engine

Under the hood, do not just store yes/no.

Use a ranking model.

Simplest version

Each battle:
	•	winner gets points
	•	loser loses points

Better version

Use Elo-style ranking.

That means:
	•	beating a strong favorite matters more
	•	beating a weak one matters less

So the app gets smarter over time and converges toward the real favorite instead of random noise.

